The NPA `physical-ai-data-factory` skill and the blueprint it documents
(`npa/workflows/workbench/npa-workflows/physical-ai-data-factory.yaml`) are an
NPA-native re-implementation on Nebius + SkyPilot of the NVIDIA Physical AI Data
Factory / Video Data Augmentation workflow. The design analysis was adapted from
NVIDIA agent skills:

  https://github.com/NVIDIA/skills
  - skills/physical-ai-video-data-augmentation   (License: CC-BY-4.0 AND Apache-2.0)
  - skills/physical-ai-infrastructure-setup-and-resilient-scaling (Apache-2.0)
  - skills/physical-ai-neural-reconstruction     (Apache-2.0)
  - skills/physical-ai-defect-image-generation   (CC-BY-4.0 AND Apache-2.0)

NPA does not use NVIDIA OSMO. The upstream skills orchestrate on OSMO; the NPA
skill orchestrates on SkyPilot and composes existing NPA workbench tools. Only
the NPA-native `physical-ai-data-factory` workflow is shipped as a live skill;
the other capabilities remain design/roadmap in
`docs/architecture/partner-skills-roadmap.md` until they land on Nebius +
SkyPilot with tests.

